    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite score of 86.34. He is our must-start anchor, benefiting from a potent combination of a favorable park adjustment and a significant SP skill edge against Lopez. Also surging is **Lawrence Butler** (69.01), who, despite hitting low in the order, receives a massive boost from a +10% park factor and a favorable matchup against Cecconi. While **Will Smith** (66.35) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (63.70) are strong starts, pay close attention to **Geraldo Perdomo**, who maintains high efficiency today by leveraging a rare platoon advantage against the typically difficult Imanaga, bolstered by an optimal #2 spot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Yainer Diaz** (48.06). He was the closest player to cracking the starting nine, but was ultimately excluded due to the stiff competition from Early, an elite arm with a 2.97 xERA that depressed the overall projected efficiency of the entire catcher/UTIL slot. We opted for higher-ceiling matchups elsewhere. Meanwhile, be cautious with **Jeremiah Jackson** (44.80) and **Wenceel Perez** (47.22); although both gain slight utility from their stolen base potential against pitchers with slower deliveries, their low base projections make them marginal starts. We are prioritizing volume and high-efficiency matchups today to maximize our 5x5 Roto standing, keeping **Daulton Varsho**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Matt Chapman** in reserve to protect our remaining game caps.",
